# Manthana — automatic-HTTPS reverse proxy (Caddy).
#
# What this does: Caddy listens on the public internet for your domain, gets + auto-renews
# a free TLS certificate from Let's Encrypt, and forwards ("reverse proxies") requests to the
# Manthana server running privately on this same machine. Engineers point their agents at
# https://<your-domain>; Caddy handles the encryption so bearer tokens never travel in plaintext.
#
# Setup (once):
#   1. Point your domain's DNS "A record" at this server's public IP.
#   2. Open ports 80 and 443 on the machine's firewall.
#   3. Run the Manthana server:   manthana-server quickstart --public-url https://<your-domain>
#   4. Run Caddy with this file:  caddy run --config ./deploy/Caddyfile
#   5. Enroll pointing at the domain:
#        manthana-server enroll acme platform --open --server-url https://<your-domain>
#
# Replace <your-domain> below with your real domain (e.g. manthana.acme.com).

<your-domain> {
	reverse_proxy 127.0.0.1:8000
}
